      "title": "How Does Baking Powder Work?",
      "description": "Baking powder makes batter and dough rise by producing carbon dioxide bubbles. Here is what triggers it, what goes wrong, and how to test your can.",
      "categoryId": "kitchen",
      "topicId": "food-science",
      "topicIds": [
